I visited Chicago for the weekend and stumbled upon this place when another restaurant I wanted to try was closed. It was very fortunate because the experience I had at this restaurant was superb!  Service: I had an excellent waitress named Alisa who was very responsive and kind who showed me the best options according to my tastes. I'd recommend asking for her if you go.  Atmosphere: we sat by the bar and I always appreciate when I can see the chefs cook. It's a sign the restaurant is confident in their cleanliness. The chefs were also friendly and social as we sat and waited for our plates.  Food: The most important factor for any restaurant is the food in my opinion. Most sushi places I go to have very subpar apps and drinks, you mainly go there for the sushi and the sushi only. This place was much different. The chile karrage chicken was a very flavorful app that was just as good as the rolls and sashimi I ordered. The cocktail list was unique and blended well together both of the ones I had were excellent.  All in all in excellent restaurant I plan on visiting them again next time I come back to Chicago!

I've been here many times. All of THOSE times are 5-stars. I just recently used their app to order for curbside pick up. The food, as usual, was awesome. The curbside pick up experience, however, was absolutely terrible! I placed my order for a 5pm pick up. I called when I arrived, as per the instructions on the app. The person that answered the phone said my order would be right out. I received a phone call back from the restaurant, from a different person, about 2 minutes later. This person said my order wasn't quite finished yet, it would be just a few minutes and they'd bring it right out. I told him, "No problem"...30 minutes later...still nothing! I called back. Yet another person answered. I told him that I had been waiting for my curbside pick up for 30 minutes. 5 more minutes...I finally got my order. I don't know what happened. But they really dropped the ball! Definitely go for the food, but NEVER use the app for a takeout order. I don't think they know how to manage it and they just have it because its a cool thing to say the have.

Had a fairly disappointing experience at SushiDokku, when visiting for Restaurant week. Several members of our party had been before so we came in with high expectations, excited to sample the wide menu offered with the prixe fixe deal. Reservation was made weeks in advance after seeing the menu offered- this is important as it came up during our visit.  Right off the bat, we notified the server that a member of our group had a shellfish allergy- so she was hoping to do the vegetarian menu, or sub in veggie items for the two dishes (oyster shooter and seared scallop) that she could not eat. I would have understood (albeit begrudgingly) if they told us you can only have veggie items if you stuck to that entire prixe fixe, but we were told that "the chef is not ready for the vegetarian menu. He won't be doing it until about half way through restaurant week". This seems wildly unprofessional, especially for somewhere with such a high price tag- the vegetarian restaurant week menu was listed WEEKS before, they were designated as a vegetarian friendly option and after checking, it was ON THE SUHIDOKKU WEBSITE as we sat there and were told it was not an option.  Our waitress on the other hand, was lovely and went back to the kitchen several times to negotiate an option that would work for us. Second time she came back and said they would let the one person order a  la carte (dont see how this is a modification) and then the third time she returned and said that we could sum the value of the two allergy triggering items, and have something off the menu at equal or lesser value. Major kudos to her for finding a solution, but we got the sense that the chef or manager or someone else up the food chain was making it really difficult for her to find an accomodation.  As for the food - the nigiri was pretty amazing, very fresh and delicious. They did mess up 2/3 of our nigiri orders but we had picked point blank and decided not to make a fuss about that, after finally getting an accomodation for the allergy. The soba noodles were kind of uninspired and I really didnt like the seared scallop in plum/apple sauce- texture was just off and the tastes didn't blend for me. The maki rolls only came in 5 pieces and were nowhere near the quality for the price. At the end of the meal, group consensus was next time we are going to Yuzu.

This is kindof a late review. I went to Sushi Dokku on a Saturday 01/12/2019 around 10:30. I  chose to go there for my 31st birthday. I found out about this place by Googling "Best Sushi Spot in Chicago " and "Best hidden Bars in Chicago. " For my birthday dinner I went to Dokku without a reservation, we were seated at the bar because my partner and I didn't want to wait to be seated (I recommend that you make a reservation before attending) The manager greeted us with a smile and made us feel very welcomed (Im so mad that I forgot his name)I'm really glad that we sat at the bar because Reid S. was our server. He was very good at multitasking, making the drinks for the restaurant and still giving us attention & providing everything that we asked for. WHEN I TRIED THE SUSHI IT WAS AMAZING! THIS PLACE HAS THE FRESHEST SUSHI I HAVE EVER TRIED! and I like exploring! Chef Mariano definitely knows what he is doing, you can tell he is so confident on his Sushi Making Skills.  He even created a roll that was not in the menu and  let me  choose the ingredients. I got to see rolls that were so colorful and different. After dinner to celebrate we head down to the bar Booze Box witch I enjoyed also. It was a very chill please and I love the fact that you can also order food down there. I recommend getting there a little earlier to get a seat because the place is pretty snugg. I definitely want to come back with several of my friends next time!
